1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:04,638
Woman: Fear, glorious fear,

2
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:08,575
it’s a natural emotion
present in all animals.

3
00:00:08,609 --> 00:00:11,779
Now i’m curious. Tell me.

4
00:00:11,812 --> 00:00:14,214
What do you think causes fear?

5
00:00:14,248 --> 00:00:16,083
( Chuckles )

6
00:00:16,116 --> 00:00:20,354
There is the kind of fear
born of animal instincts

7
00:00:20,387 --> 00:00:21,722
and the kind of fear

8
00:00:21,755 --> 00:00:25,392
born of a rational mind
that terrorizes humans.

9
00:00:25,425 --> 00:00:29,696
Namely when you encounter
a foe stronger than yourself

10
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:31,465
and realize you have no way

11
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:34,468
of fighting back
against the unknown,

12
00:00:34,501 --> 00:00:38,572
your helplessness
begins to sink in

13
00:00:38,605 --> 00:00:43,110
and evokes inside of you
a terrible and paralyzing fear.

14
00:00:43,143 --> 00:00:44,745
( Chuckles )

15
00:00:44,778 --> 00:00:46,747
( Woman #2 moaning )

16
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:50,484
Woman #1: When you are
faced with such fear,

17
00:00:50,517 --> 00:00:53,587
you have a number of options
before you from which to choose.

18
00:00:54,655 --> 00:00:57,324
You might struggle, resist,

19
00:00:57,357 --> 00:00:59,759
flee, accept, or freeze.

20
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:02,329
But upon meeting lord dio,

21
00:01:02,362 --> 00:01:05,498
a new,
unexpected reaction arises.

22
00:01:05,532 --> 00:01:07,801
You feel joy!

23
00:01:07,835 --> 00:01:10,538
Dio: How do you think
most people act

24
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:12,706
once they feel joy in fear?

25
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:15,108
It’s an interesting experience.

26
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:17,511
Woman #1: Our friend
is currently on the plane

27
00:01:17,544 --> 00:01:20,414
that joestar and
the others have boarded.

28
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:22,282
He’ll greet them accordingly,

29
00:01:22,316 --> 00:01:24,685
and they will find it
utterly impossible

30
00:01:24,718 --> 00:01:28,455
to reach their final destination
in one piece.

31
00:01:28,488 --> 00:01:31,591
( Cackles )

32
00:01:41,902 --> 00:01:44,438
( Insect buzzing )

33
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:50,410
Kakyoin: Hmm?

34
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:52,313
- ( Gasps )
- Avdol: Hmm?

35
00:01:52,346 --> 00:01:53,314
( Both sigh )

36
00:01:53,347 --> 00:01:55,349
♪

37
00:01:58,519 --> 00:02:00,521
( Buzzing continues )

38
00:02:07,728 --> 00:02:09,630
Jotaro: A rhino beetle?

39
00:02:09,663 --> 00:02:13,133
No. It’s a stag beetle.

40
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:15,269
Joseph: Hey, avdol,
is that a stand?

41
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:18,172
Are we already encountering
another stand user?

42
00:02:18,205 --> 00:02:19,673
Avdol: It’s possible.

43
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:22,409
This could be a stand that
takes the shape of an insect.

44
00:02:22,442 --> 00:02:25,845
What the--it hid
in the shadow of the seats.

45
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:28,849
Avdol: Damn.
It could be anywhere.

46
00:02:32,519 --> 00:02:33,754
( Beetle chirps )

47
00:02:33,787 --> 00:02:36,523
Kakyoin: Jojo,
it’s next to your head!

48
00:02:36,557 --> 00:02:37,825
Look to your right!

49
00:02:37,858 --> 00:02:39,860
♪

50
00:02:47,201 --> 00:02:49,203
( Singing in Japanese )

51
00:03:22,803 --> 00:03:27,308
Kakyoin: Whoa. It’s so huge.
That thing has to be a stand.

52
00:03:27,341 --> 00:03:29,710
No doubt. It’s here for us.

53
00:03:31,612 --> 00:03:32,947
Jotaro: That’s disgusting.

54
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:35,683
Just sit tight.
I’ll take care of it.

55
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:37,318
Avdol: Be extremely careful.

56
00:03:37,351 --> 00:03:39,920
I’ve heard that there is
a user of an insect stand

57
00:03:39,953 --> 00:03:41,621
that likes
to rip out the tongues

58
00:03:41,655 --> 00:03:43,657
of his victims before they die.

59
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:44,691
Jotaro: Star platinum!

60
00:03:45,993 --> 00:03:47,294
( All gasp )

61
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:49,329
Avdol: It dodged you.

62
00:03:49,363 --> 00:03:51,565
I-I can’t believe it.

63
00:03:51,598 --> 00:03:53,867
It’s faster than star platinum,
a stand that has

64
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:56,570
the speed and precision
to grab a flying bullet.

65
00:03:56,603 --> 00:03:58,572
Kakyoin: Then there’s
no doubt about it.

66
00:03:58,605 --> 00:04:00,807
That bug can only be a stand.

67
00:04:00,841 --> 00:04:02,576
Where is he?
Where is he hiding?

68
00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:04,911
Where is the one
who’s controlling it?

69
00:04:04,945 --> 00:04:06,747
We need to find him.

70
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,515
It’s getting ready to attack!

71
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:12,019
( Star platinum roars )

72
00:04:12,052 --> 00:04:13,687
Jotaro: No, damn it.

73
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,689
- Joseph: Jotaro!
- Avdol: Jojo!

74
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:20,761
( Jotaro shuddering )

75
00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:21,795
( Star platinum growls )

76
00:04:23,564 --> 00:04:25,833
Joseph: Star platinum
stopped it with its teeth

77
00:04:25,866 --> 00:04:27,267
just in the Nick of time.

78
00:04:27,301 --> 00:04:28,836
Avdol: Just as I feared,

79
00:04:28,869 --> 00:04:31,004
it’s going
after jotaro’s stand’s tongue.

80
00:04:31,038 --> 00:04:34,975
It’s him, represented by
the tower card of the tarot,

81
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:38,411
symbolizing calamity and
the interruption of a journey.

82
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:39,980
This stand is called...

83
00:04:42,382 --> 00:04:43,850
Tower of gray!

84
00:04:43,884 --> 00:04:45,919
( Tower of gray chitters )

85
00:04:45,953 --> 00:04:47,521
Avdol: Tower of gray
is responsible

86
00:04:47,554 --> 00:04:49,056
for countless mass murders,

87
00:04:49,089 --> 00:04:51,425
which he made to look
like unfortunate accidents.

88
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,493
The plane crash
last year in england

89
00:04:53,527 --> 00:04:55,929
that caused over 300 deaths
was likely his work.

90
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:58,499
And how many more
have there been over the years?

91
00:04:58,532 --> 00:05:02,002
I’d heard rumors, but to think
he’s teamed up with dio...

92
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:04,971
Jotaro: Ora!

93
00:05:05,005 --> 00:05:07,007
( Yelling )

94
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:12,513
Avdol: It dodged
that attack, too?

95
00:05:12,546 --> 00:05:14,014
Not just from the single hand,

96
00:05:14,047 --> 00:05:17,918
but it also dodged
a two-fisted barrage of blows.

97
00:05:17,951 --> 00:05:19,653
I-it’s so fast.

98
00:05:19,686 --> 00:05:22,822
( Tower of gray laughs )
Even if you had 10 guns

99
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:24,858
to shoot bullets
from one centimeter away,

100
00:05:24,892 --> 00:05:27,561
they would not be able
to touch my stand.

101
00:05:27,594 --> 00:05:30,597
Not that you could kill a stand
with a gun, anyways.

102
00:05:30,631 --> 00:05:33,734
You’re all going to die with
the rest of these weaklings.

103
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:37,337
Joseph: He has to be
on this plane with us.

104
00:05:37,371 --> 00:05:41,542
Who is it? Who is the one
controlling the stand?

105
00:05:44,578 --> 00:05:47,081
Which one
of the passengers is he?

106
00:05:47,114 --> 00:05:50,584
If we can track him down,
we can squash him.

107
00:05:51,585 --> 00:05:52,586
( Jotaro gasps )

108
00:05:52,619 --> 00:05:53,687
It disappeared again.

109
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:56,323
( Buzzing )

110
00:05:57,891 --> 00:05:58,959
( Kakyoin gasps )

111
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:00,961
Heads up. It’s over there now.

112
00:06:00,994 --> 00:06:02,762
( Tower of gray laughs )

113
00:06:05,132 --> 00:06:07,568
Jotaro: What’s it
planning to do?

114
00:06:07,601 --> 00:06:09,903
Avdol: No. It can’t be.

115
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:14,908
( All gasp )

116
00:06:14,942 --> 00:06:16,811
( Tower of gray laughs )

117
00:06:16,844 --> 00:06:18,479
Bingo.

118
00:06:18,512 --> 00:06:19,480
Got their tongues.

119
00:06:19,513 --> 00:06:22,116
Now for the best part.

120
00:06:29,423 --> 00:06:30,891
Narrator: Massacre--

121
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:33,994
its definition,
to kill everyone.

122
00:06:34,027 --> 00:06:36,496
Kakyoin: No.
It actually did it.

123
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:40,067
Avdol: Fine.
I’ll burn that damn bug alive!

124
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,868
Go, magician’s red!

125
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:43,036
( Magician’s red squawks )

126
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:45,940
Kakyoin: Avdol,
just hold on a second.

127
00:06:45,973 --> 00:06:47,608
Avdol: Hmm?

128
00:06:47,641 --> 00:06:49,643
( Man groaning )

129
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:53,547
It’s so damn noisy
on this flight.

130
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:56,817
- What’s with all the ruckus?
- Kakyoin: Be careful!

131
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:59,019
Man: Might as well
go to the bathroom.

132
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:04,992
Why’s this wet?

133
00:07:05,025 --> 00:07:07,094
What’s with
all this slimy stuff?

134
00:07:07,127 --> 00:07:09,830
"M"--( Sniffs )

135
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:12,566
"A-s"--( Screams )

136
00:07:14,168 --> 00:07:16,170
Blood! This is blood!

137
00:07:16,203 --> 00:07:17,571
( Gasps )

138
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:19,706
Kakyoin: Atemi.

139
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,442
We have to defeat it

140
00:07:21,475 --> 00:07:23,577
before the other passengers
start to panic.

141
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,145
Easier said than done, though.

142
00:07:25,179 --> 00:07:26,747
Mr. Avdol...

143
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:29,616
Using an active stand
like your magician’s red

144
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:32,153
inside an airborne plane
could make it explode,

145
00:07:32,186 --> 00:07:33,788
killing all of us.

146
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:36,222
Jojo, if your power were
to rip a hole in the fuselage,

147
00:07:36,256 --> 00:07:37,858
- it’d be a catastrophe.
- ( Buzzing )

148
00:07:37,891 --> 00:07:40,761
This calls for
a quiet and discreet stand.

149
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:44,131
My hierophant green
is most suited to defeating it.

150
00:07:44,164 --> 00:07:46,133
Let me take care
of the pest control.

151
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:48,068
( Tower of gray laughs )

152
00:07:48,101 --> 00:07:50,203
Noriaki kakyoin, eh?

153
00:07:50,237 --> 00:07:53,540
I’ve heard all about you
from lord dio.

154
00:07:53,574 --> 00:07:55,176
Don’t bother.

155
00:07:55,209 --> 00:07:58,746
You think you have
silence on your side,

156
00:07:58,779 --> 00:08:02,950
but your stand
cannot keep up with my speed!

157
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,586
Kakyoin: You sure about that?

158
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,489
Emerald splash!

159
00:08:09,523 --> 00:08:11,525
( Tower of gray laughing )

160
00:08:13,594 --> 00:08:16,130
Kakyoin: Hmm?
Emerald splash again!

161
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:20,267
( Tower of gray laughing )

162
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:24,104
You seem to think you can hit me
if you fire enough shots,

163
00:08:24,137 --> 00:08:26,239
but you haven’t hit me at all.

164
00:08:26,273 --> 00:08:28,709
- Kakyoin: Huh?
- Avdol: Not good.

165
00:08:28,742 --> 00:08:30,744
It’s dodging
everything he throws at it.

166
00:08:32,779 --> 00:08:35,248
- ( Kakyoin gags )
- Jotaro: Kakyoin.

167
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:38,885
( Tower of gray laughs )

168
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:41,755
I’m just too fast for you.

169
00:08:41,788 --> 00:08:44,791
You’re way too slow
to get a bingo.

170
00:08:44,825 --> 00:08:46,760
And, kakyoin...

171
00:08:46,793 --> 00:08:48,595
With my next attack,

172
00:08:48,629 --> 00:08:50,898
i’ll stab your stand’s tongue
with this tower needle

173
00:08:50,931 --> 00:08:53,667
and rip it out.
Won’t that be fun?

174
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:57,037
Kakyoin: Emerald splash!

175
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:59,806
Tower of gray: Don’t you get it?
( Laughing )

176
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:03,009
Avdol: Damn. Impossible.

177
00:09:03,043 --> 00:09:05,312
How can he win if his attacks
don’t find their Mark?

178
00:09:05,345 --> 00:09:07,814
Tower of gray:
You’ll go mad from the pain

179
00:09:07,848 --> 00:09:09,817
once this rips its tongue out.
( Laughs )

180
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:11,919
How exquisite.

181
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:13,720
Kakyoin: Is that right?

182
00:09:13,754 --> 00:09:16,323
If its tongue’s ripped out,
i’ll go mad from the pain?

183
00:09:16,356 --> 00:09:19,993
My hierophant green
will go mad, all right.

184
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:23,797
( Tower of gray screams )

185
00:09:23,831 --> 00:09:25,866
What?

186
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:28,735
Kakyoin: If it rips you apart,
it’ll go mad...

187
00:09:28,769 --> 00:09:30,804
From pure joy.

188
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:34,241
( Tower of gray screaming )

189
00:09:37,778 --> 00:09:38,912
Kakyoin: His appendages

190
00:09:38,946 --> 00:09:40,614
had already slipped
beneath the seats.

191
00:09:40,647 --> 00:09:43,350
I just needed enough time
to set up my little trap.

192
00:09:43,383 --> 00:09:46,920
You didn’t realize
I was using my emerald splash

193
00:09:46,954 --> 00:09:49,190
to keep you in one spot?

194
00:09:54,294 --> 00:09:57,597
( Man gags )

195
00:09:57,631 --> 00:09:58,699
Joseph: What the...

196
00:10:00,734 --> 00:10:04,638
Kakyoin: So that geezer
was the user all along, huh?

197
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:07,841
Heh. Guess I should
have expected as much.

198
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:11,112
A repulsive stand
usually has a repulsive user.

199
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:16,116
Well, that’s strange.

200
00:10:16,149 --> 00:10:19,819
It doesn’t look like he had
dio’s flesh bud in his forehead.

201
00:10:19,853 --> 00:10:22,122
Avdol: Tower of gray
was always evil.

202
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:24,124
He killed tourists
by the hundreds

203
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:25,792
and got paid for it.

204
00:10:25,826 --> 00:10:27,294
He’d make it
look like an accident

205
00:10:27,327 --> 00:10:28,929
and got away with it every time.

206
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:31,298
I’m sure dio
was able to use him,

207
00:10:31,331 --> 00:10:34,901
because he was easily bought
and blinded by greed.

208
00:10:34,935 --> 00:10:36,270
( Plane creaking )

209
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:37,604
Joseph: Eh?

210
00:10:39,173 --> 00:10:40,775
Something’s wrong.

211
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:43,310
It could be my imagination,
but I get the feeling

212
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:45,245
this plane isn’t
flying straight anymore.

213
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,648
♪

214
00:10:49,049 --> 00:10:52,352
It’s crooked.
No doubt about it.

215
00:10:52,386 --> 00:10:54,021
Huh? It can’t be.

216
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:58,725
- Jotaro: Hmm?
- ( Kakyoin sighs )

217
00:10:58,759 --> 00:11:00,995
Attendant: Sorry, sir.
You can’t be up here.

218
00:11:01,028 --> 00:11:03,764
The cockpit is up ahead,
so passengers may not enter.

219
00:11:03,797 --> 00:11:05,098
Joseph: I know that.

220
00:11:05,132 --> 00:11:07,701
Attendant: S-sir, wait.

221
00:11:07,734 --> 00:11:09,736
( Attendants gasping )

222
00:11:13,774 --> 00:11:16,343
Both: Oh. He’s so handsome.

223
00:11:16,376 --> 00:11:18,778
Jotaro: Move it, bitch.

224
00:11:18,812 --> 00:11:20,347
Attendant #2: What a shock.

225
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:21,381
Kakyoin: Whoa, there.

226
00:11:21,415 --> 00:11:23,150
Sorry, ladies.

227
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:26,687
His disrespectful behavior
towards you two is incorrigible,

228
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,789
but we have an emergency
on our hands.

229
00:11:28,822 --> 00:11:29,923
( Both sigh )

230
00:11:29,957 --> 00:11:31,392
Kakyoin:
Please forgive him, for me.

231
00:11:31,425 --> 00:11:33,193
Both: Okay.

232
00:11:33,227 --> 00:11:35,763
Joseph: Damn it!
This is horrible!

233
00:11:36,997 --> 00:11:39,399
We’ve been had!

234
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,468
Jotaro: Their tongues
have been ripped out.

235
00:11:41,502 --> 00:11:43,004
That rhino bastard.

236
00:11:43,036 --> 00:11:45,305
He killed the pilots
before we knew he was here.

237
00:11:45,339 --> 00:11:46,140
( Both gasp )

238
00:11:49,376 --> 00:11:51,712
Joseph: Hmm.
We’re losing altitude fast.

239
00:11:51,745 --> 00:11:54,414
The autopilot’s
been destroyed as well.

240
00:11:57,150 --> 00:12:00,120
Damn it, we’re going to crash.

241
00:12:00,153 --> 00:12:03,423
( User laughing )

242
00:12:03,457 --> 00:12:04,458
Jotaro: What?

243
00:12:08,195 --> 00:12:10,431
User: My stand is
the tower card,

244
00:12:10,464 --> 00:12:11,899
which signifies
horrible accidents

245
00:12:11,932 --> 00:12:13,500
and the end of journey.

246
00:12:13,534 --> 00:12:17,471
I’ll keep you from lord dio
if it’s the last thing I do.

247
00:12:17,504 --> 00:12:20,340
Even if you manage
to survive the crash,

248
00:12:20,374 --> 00:12:23,510
you’re still
10,000 kilometers from Egypt.

249
00:12:23,544 --> 00:12:26,013
Those who swore loyalty
to lord dio

250
00:12:26,046 --> 00:12:27,281
will pursue you relentlessly.

251
00:12:27,314 --> 00:12:29,483
You don’t stand
a chance in hell.

252
00:12:29,516 --> 00:12:31,985
There are stands in this world

253
00:12:32,019 --> 00:12:35,356
with powers that defy
the very limits of imagination.

254
00:12:35,389 --> 00:12:39,193
Lord dio’s power is the one
that rules over all of them.

255
00:12:39,226 --> 00:12:41,295
He is the master of stands,

256
00:12:41,328 --> 00:12:44,364
reigning over the world
like a god among mortals.

257
00:12:44,398 --> 00:12:46,967
There’s no way
you’ll reach him alive.

258
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,170
You bastards
won’t even see Egypt.

259
00:12:50,204 --> 00:12:53,174
Your deaths
will be swift and painful!

260
00:12:53,207 --> 00:12:54,275
( Laughs )

261
00:12:54,308 --> 00:12:55,109
( Both gasp )

262
00:12:57,911 --> 00:13:00,781
Jotaro: You’re
definitely professionals.

263
00:13:00,814 --> 00:13:02,349
Good thing you didn’t scream.

264
00:13:02,382 --> 00:13:05,051
That annoys me
all to freaking hell.

265
00:13:05,085 --> 00:13:06,787
Now, i’ve got a request.

266
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,355
This heap’s gonna hit water,

267
00:13:08,388 --> 00:13:10,557
and this old man’s
gonna land her there.

268
00:13:10,591 --> 00:13:12,159
Joseph: Huh?

269
00:13:12,192 --> 00:13:14,161
Jotaro: Go put life jackets
on the other passengers,

270
00:13:14,194 --> 00:13:15,429
and make sure
they’re buckled up.

271
00:13:15,462 --> 00:13:17,030
Attendant #1: Uh, yes, sir.

272
00:13:17,064 --> 00:13:18,566
Jotaro: You got this?

273
00:13:18,599 --> 00:13:20,167
Joseph: Mm...

274
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:23,036
I have some experience
with prop planes, but this...

275
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:24,038
Kakyoin: Prop planes?

276
00:13:24,071 --> 00:13:25,973
Joseph: But, jotaro,

277
00:13:26,006 --> 00:13:28,242
this’ll make
three plane crashes for me.

278
00:13:28,275 --> 00:13:30,244
Have you ever heard of someone

279
00:13:30,277 --> 00:13:32,513
being in a plane crash
three times,

280
00:13:32,546 --> 00:13:34,915
let alone surviving each one?

281
00:13:34,948 --> 00:13:36,850
( Men sigh )

282
00:13:37,985 --> 00:13:39,353
Jotaro: That settles it.

283
00:13:39,386 --> 00:13:43,023
I’m never riding in a plane
with you again.

284
00:13:45,792 --> 00:13:47,294
Er thrumming )

285
00:13:53,534 --> 00:13:54,802
Narrator: The plane landed

286
00:13:54,835 --> 00:13:58,238
35 kilometers
off the coast of Hong Kong.

287
00:13:58,272 --> 00:13:59,473
Jotaro and the others

288
00:13:59,506 --> 00:14:01,608
had no choice
but to head to the city.

289
00:14:01,642 --> 00:14:03,577
Reporter: ...South of Hong Kong,
near lamma island.

290
00:14:03,610 --> 00:14:06,346
Rescue efforts
are now under way.

291
00:14:07,514 --> 00:14:09,750
Narrator: Hong Kong,
Hong Kong island,

292
00:14:09,783 --> 00:14:11,952
kowloon, the new territories.

293
00:14:11,985 --> 00:14:15,689
With more than 235
individual islands in the area,

294
00:14:15,722 --> 00:14:17,324
its breathtaking nightscape

295
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:20,360
is known the world over
as the million-dollar view.

296
00:14:20,394 --> 00:14:23,898
Joseph: Yeah, no problem.
That’ll be fine.

297
00:14:23,931 --> 00:14:26,967
Please make sure the only ones
aboard are us and the crew.

298
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:31,671
Right. There’s been enough
collateral damage because of us.

299
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:32,673
By the way...

300
00:14:32,706 --> 00:14:34,274
Shopkeeper: Hey, big guy.

301
00:14:34,308 --> 00:14:35,776
Jotaro: Hmm?

302
00:14:35,809 --> 00:14:38,578
Shopkeeper: You guys aren’t
from around here, are you?

303
00:14:38,612 --> 00:14:40,848
Want some rice porridge?
Can’t come to Hong Kong

304
00:14:40,881 --> 00:14:43,283
and not try our rice porridge
and dim sum.

305
00:14:43,317 --> 00:14:44,618
We have some hot cola, too.

306
00:14:44,651 --> 00:14:46,720
Kakyoin: Rice porridge? Not bad.

307
00:14:46,753 --> 00:14:48,455
Did you know, jojo,

308
00:14:48,488 --> 00:14:51,958
unlike in Japan, rice porridge
is a staple food in Hong Kong.

309
00:14:51,992 --> 00:14:53,627
To some, it’s quite a delicacy.

310
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:55,495
One bowl, the popular way,

311
00:14:55,529 --> 00:14:57,898
with pork and century egg,
if you have it.

312
00:14:57,931 --> 00:14:58,999
Shopkeeper: Coming right up.

313
00:14:59,032 --> 00:15:00,634
Avdol: In that case, i’ll have--

314
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:02,669
Joseph: Hey! What?

315
00:15:02,703 --> 00:15:04,371
You boys think
we have time to eat?

316
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:05,572
We’re going to my old favorite.

317
00:15:05,606 --> 00:15:07,308
You can wait
to stuff your faces there.

318
00:15:07,341 --> 00:15:09,376
Shopkeeper:
Hey, you dandy guy over there,

319
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:12,345
I know you’d be interested
in some Hong Kong hot cola.

320
00:15:12,379 --> 00:15:14,348
Joseph: Hot cola?
That’s blasphemy.

321
00:15:14,381 --> 00:15:16,617
Everyone knows
it’s supposed to be cold.

322
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:19,486
Jotaro: Old man,
who were you just callin’?

323
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,955
Joseph: Hmm? Oh, that.

324
00:15:20,988 --> 00:15:23,624
I’ll explain
when we get to the restaurant.

325
00:15:23,657 --> 00:15:24,625
Be patient.

326
00:15:24,658 --> 00:15:26,627
We need to work out a plan

327
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:29,496
that’ll get us to Egypt as
safely and quickly as possible.

328
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:31,432
More users
are bound to come after us,

329
00:15:31,465 --> 00:15:32,633
and that could cost lives.

330
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:34,902
Kakyoin: Right. A plan.

331
00:15:34,935 --> 00:15:36,637
Avdol: I agree with you.

332
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:38,805
We can’t allow
any more innocent civilians

333
00:15:38,839 --> 00:15:40,741
to be hurt
because of our failure.

334
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:43,543
The quickest way would be
by plane, but that’s out.

335
00:15:43,577 --> 00:15:44,778
Joseph: Indeed.

336
00:15:44,811 --> 00:15:47,547
It’s now become
completely impossible

337
00:15:47,581 --> 00:15:49,550
for us to fly to Egypt.

338
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:53,554
You see, if we encounter
a stand user like the last one

339
00:15:53,587 --> 00:15:56,023
on a commercial flight,
we’ll cause a disaster,

340
00:15:56,056 --> 00:15:59,660
one that will harm many people
and might kill many more.

341
00:15:59,693 --> 00:16:01,295
With that in mind,

342
00:16:01,328 --> 00:16:04,064
we’ll have to get to Egypt
by either land or sea.

343
00:16:04,097 --> 00:16:05,599
Avdol: I hear you,

344
00:16:05,632 --> 00:16:09,069
but if we fail to find dio
within 50 days...

345
00:16:09,102 --> 00:16:10,670
Hmm.

346
00:16:10,704 --> 00:16:12,873
( Both grunt )

347
00:16:12,906 --> 00:16:14,908
Kakyoin: If we could have
stayed on that plane,

348
00:16:14,942 --> 00:16:17,478
we’d probably be in Cairo,
and this would be over.

349
00:16:17,511 --> 00:16:19,880
( Jotaro sighs )

350
00:16:19,913 --> 00:16:21,348
( Joseph sighs )

351
00:16:21,381 --> 00:16:23,316
♪

352
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,452
I’m well aware of that.

353
00:16:25,485 --> 00:16:28,488
However, it’s too soon
to worry about it.

354
00:16:28,522 --> 00:16:29,490
( Men gasp )

355
00:16:29,523 --> 00:16:30,991
Joseph: One hundred years ago,

356
00:16:31,024 --> 00:16:33,793
Jules verne wrote
"around the world in 80 days,"

357
00:16:33,827 --> 00:16:37,931
a story about a man who travels
40,000 kilometers in 11 weeks

358
00:16:37,965 --> 00:16:40,601
using nothing
but trains and steamboats,

359
00:16:40,634 --> 00:16:44,705
we may not have a plane,
but we still have 50 days.

360
00:16:44,738 --> 00:16:47,341
We’ll be able to travel
the 10,000 kilometers to Egypt.

361
00:16:47,374 --> 00:16:48,809
And as for the route
we’ll take...

362
00:16:48,842 --> 00:16:50,610
♪

363
00:16:50,644 --> 00:16:53,847
I say we go by sea.

364
00:16:53,881 --> 00:16:56,417
We’ll charter
a suitably sized boat,

365
00:16:56,450 --> 00:17:00,087
go around the malay peninsula,
and cross the Indian ocean,

366
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:03,090
"a silk road of the sea,"
as it were.

367
00:17:03,123 --> 00:17:05,826
Avdol: I believe
that is best as well.

368
00:17:05,859 --> 00:17:07,828
Crossing by land
could be difficult,

369
00:17:07,861 --> 00:17:10,530
and we’d have to cross
the himalayas or the desert.

370
00:17:10,564 --> 00:17:12,800
If we ran into trouble,
we’d lose a lot of time.

371
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,368
There are too many dangers.

372
00:17:14,401 --> 00:17:16,570
Kakyoin: I haven’t been
to any of those places

373
00:17:16,603 --> 00:17:18,839
using either route before,
so I really don’t know.

374
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:21,375
I’ll leave it
up to the two of you.

375
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:23,577
( Jotaro sighs ) Same with me.

376
00:17:23,610 --> 00:17:25,145
Joseph: Then it’s decided.

377
00:17:25,179 --> 00:17:27,648
Now the greatest danger
that we’ll face

378
00:17:27,681 --> 00:17:30,918
will be the stand users
that dio sends against us.

379
00:17:30,951 --> 00:17:35,389
We’ll have to do our best to get
to Egypt without being spotted.

380
00:17:35,422 --> 00:17:37,791
♪

381
00:17:37,824 --> 00:17:39,859
♪

382
00:17:39,893 --> 00:17:41,995
- ( Jotaro gasps )
- ( Kakyoin chuckles )

383
00:17:42,029 --> 00:17:43,531
Don’t be so jumpy.

384
00:17:43,564 --> 00:17:45,833
This is just to let them know
we want more tea.

385
00:17:45,866 --> 00:17:47,534
If you do this in Hong Kong,

386
00:17:47,568 --> 00:17:49,770
they’ll usually bring you more
within a few seconds.

387
00:17:54,174 --> 00:17:55,742
Also...

388
00:17:55,776 --> 00:17:58,779
Anytime the server pours
some tea into your cup...

389
00:18:00,214 --> 00:18:01,449
Tap the table.

390
00:18:01,481 --> 00:18:03,450
It’s a way of saying thank you.

391
00:18:03,483 --> 00:18:04,684
( Waitress giggles )

392
00:18:05,986 --> 00:18:08,589
Man: Excuse me.
Sorry to be a bother.

393
00:18:08,622 --> 00:18:10,190
I’m a tourist from France.

394
00:18:10,224 --> 00:18:13,194
Could you help me out?
My Chinese is a bit rusty,

395
00:18:13,227 --> 00:18:16,697
and i’m having a hard time
with the characters on the menu.

396
00:18:16,730 --> 00:18:18,532
Could you help me decipher it?

397
00:18:18,565 --> 00:18:19,800
Jotaro: You’re annoying.

398
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,034
Go away.

399
00:18:21,068 --> 00:18:23,170
Joseph: Come now, jotaro.
It’s fine.

400
00:18:23,203 --> 00:18:26,106
Try to be nice to the man.

401
00:18:26,139 --> 00:18:29,042
I’ve been to Hong Kong
many times over the years.

402
00:18:29,076 --> 00:18:31,979
I can at least read
the characters on the menus.

403
00:18:32,012 --> 00:18:33,547
Why don’t you join us?

404
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:36,016
So what do you want to order?

405
00:18:36,049 --> 00:18:40,153
Dish with shrimp, duck,
shark fin, and mushrooms?

406
00:18:40,187 --> 00:18:42,923
Hmm.

407
00:18:42,956 --> 00:18:44,791
We’ll have this, this, and this,

408
00:18:44,825 --> 00:18:46,894
and might as well
get some of these.

409
00:18:46,927 --> 00:18:48,796
Oh, and this.

410
00:18:48,829 --> 00:18:50,464
Waiter: Mm-hmm.

411
00:18:50,497 --> 00:18:51,965
( Gong chimes )

412
00:18:51,999 --> 00:18:53,033
Avdol: These look like dishes

413
00:18:53,066 --> 00:18:54,668
with beef, fish...

414
00:18:54,701 --> 00:18:56,469
Clams, and frog.

415
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:59,106
Kakyoin: Indeed, this is
quite different from our order.

416
00:18:59,139 --> 00:19:01,675
Jotaro: I knew this
would happen, damn it.

417
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:03,476
( Man gasps )

418
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,479
( Joseph laughs )

419
00:19:05,512 --> 00:19:07,014
Well, it makes no difference.

420
00:19:07,047 --> 00:19:08,682
It’s all on me, boys.

421
00:19:08,715 --> 00:19:10,984
Besides, it doesn’t matter
what you order.

422
00:19:11,018 --> 00:19:13,254
It’s all delicious. ( Laughs )

423
00:19:13,287 --> 00:19:15,523
All right, everyone. Dig in.

424
00:19:17,090 --> 00:19:18,525
( Men gasp )

425
00:19:21,628 --> 00:19:23,663
Kakyoin: Oh. This is...

426
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:29,236
Joseph: You see that?
And you were worried.

427
00:19:29,269 --> 00:19:30,971
( Laughs )

428
00:19:31,004 --> 00:19:33,006
Man: Well, they’ve certainly
taken a lot of time

429
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,242
to prepare this.
It’s almost artistic.

430
00:19:35,275 --> 00:19:40,814
Take these carrots, for example,
cut into perfect little stars.

431
00:19:40,848 --> 00:19:43,517
In fact,
it reminds me of something.

432
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:45,652
( Men gasp )

433
00:19:45,686 --> 00:19:47,021
Man: I remember now.

434
00:19:47,054 --> 00:19:48,956
Someone I know has a Mark,

435
00:19:48,989 --> 00:19:52,059
a birthmark just like this
on the back of their neck.

436
00:19:52,092 --> 00:19:54,761
Know anyone like that?

437
00:19:55,863 --> 00:19:57,298
( Joseph growls )

438
00:19:57,331 --> 00:19:59,533
- ( Avdol growls )
- ( Jotaro sighs )

439
00:19:59,566 --> 00:20:01,001
Kakyoin: Are you another...

440
00:20:01,034 --> 00:20:02,035
Enemy?

441
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:05,539
( Man chuckles )

442
00:20:08,876 --> 00:20:11,011
( Joseph gasps )

443
00:20:11,044 --> 00:20:12,979
Avdol: Mr. Joestar, look out!

444
00:20:13,013 --> 00:20:15,048
- Joseph: It’s a stand!
- ( Metal hand clangs )

445
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,552
Avdol: Magician’s red,
come forth!

446
00:20:18,585 --> 00:20:20,287
( Magician’s red squawks )

447
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:21,555
( Stand grunts )

448
00:20:24,124 --> 00:20:25,592
Avdol: What the hell?

449
00:20:27,361 --> 00:20:30,297
You were right,
another stand user.

450
00:20:34,268 --> 00:20:35,669
- ( Joseph gasps )
- Kakyoin: Whoa.

451
00:20:35,702 --> 00:20:37,904
He has such speed
with his sword.

452
00:20:40,007 --> 00:20:42,009
Man: My stand
is the chariot card,

453
00:20:42,042 --> 00:20:44,578
and his name is silver chariot.

454
00:20:44,611 --> 00:20:46,179
Mohammed avdol,

455
00:20:46,213 --> 00:20:49,616
it seems that I will be
disposing of you first.

456
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:52,653
I’ve carved a burning clock
into that table.

457
00:20:52,686 --> 00:20:57,724
Before that clock strikes 12:00,
you will be a dead man.

458
00:21:04,398 --> 00:21:06,600
♪

459
00:21:18,312 --> 00:21:20,781
♪ All the old paintings
on the tomb ♪

460
00:21:20,814 --> 00:21:23,050
♪ they do the sand dance,
don’t you know ♪

461
00:21:23,083 --> 00:21:24,184
♪ if they move too quick

462
00:21:24,218 --> 00:21:25,753
♪ oh, whey, oh

463
00:21:25,786 --> 00:21:27,721
♪ they’re falling down
like a domino ♪

464
00:21:27,754 --> 00:21:30,056
♪ all the bazaar men
by the nile ♪

465
00:21:30,090 --> 00:21:32,159
♪ they got the money on a bet

466
00:21:32,192 --> 00:21:33,360
♪ gold crocodiles

467
00:21:33,393 --> 00:21:34,895
♪ oh, whey, oh

468
00:21:34,928 --> 00:21:36,963
♪ they snap their teeth
on your cigarette ♪

469
00:21:36,997 --> 00:21:39,099
♪ foreign types
with the hookah pipes say ♪

470
00:21:39,132 --> 00:21:41,368
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

471
00:21:41,401 --> 00:21:45,105
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

472
00:21:46,206 --> 00:21:48,842
♪ walk like an Egyptian

473
00:22:00,087 --> 00:22:02,790
♪ The blond waitresses
take their trays ♪

474
00:22:02,823 --> 00:22:04,892
♪ they spin around,
and they cross the floor ♪

475
00:22:04,925 --> 00:22:06,160
♪ they’ve got the moves

476
00:22:06,193 --> 00:22:07,161
♪ oh, whey, oh

477
00:22:07,194 --> 00:22:08,195
♪ you drop your drink

478
00:22:08,228 --> 00:22:09,696
♪ then they bring you more

479
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:11,966
♪ all the school kids
so sick of books ♪

480
00:22:11,999 --> 00:22:14,168
♪ they like the punk
and the metal band ♪

481
00:22:14,201 --> 00:22:15,402
♪ when the buzzer rings

482
00:22:15,435 --> 00:22:16,903
♪ oh, whey, oh

483
00:22:16,937 --> 00:22:18,906
♪ they’re walking
like an Egyptian ♪

484
00:22:18,939 --> 00:22:21,041
♪ all the kids
in the marketplace say ♪

485
00:22:21,074 --> 00:22:23,276
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

486
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:28,081
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

487
00:22:28,115 --> 00:22:31,185
♪ walk like an Egyptian

